README — Household Profit per Acre, Community Merge, Education/Employment & sec1 Roster
1. Overview

This part of the project builds a household-level analytic dataset with profit per acre, merges it with community-level EA data, then with education/employment data from a teammate, and finally with household roster data (sec1).

At the very end, you get a fully enriched modeling dataset at the household level.

High-level flow:

Build household farm area (acres) from sec8b.dta.

Build household profit per acre from agg2.dta + land acres.

Remove extreme outliers & merge with EA-level community master + region/district → Final_EDA_master_file.rds.

Teammate merges in education & employment → project_EDA_final 1.rds.

You merge household roster (sec1) on top → project_EDA_final_with_sec1.rds (final modeling file).

