4. Script Details
4.1 Profit_per_acre.R

Purpose: Build total farm land area in acres per household.

Key Steps:

Load sec8b.dta.

Keep only:

clust (cluster/EA ID)

nh (household within cluster)

s8bq4a (area value)

s8bq4b (unit code)

Create unique HH ID:

clust_nh = paste0(clust, "_", nh)


Convert to acres (land_area_acres) via s8bq4b:

1 = Acres → as-is

2 = Poles → treat as acres

3 = Ropes → 9 ropes = 1 acre → s8bq4a / 9

4 = Other → NA

Aggregate to household-level:

total_farm_area_acres = sum(land_area_acres, na.rm = TRUE) per clust_nh.

Output:

sec8b_farm_land_household_level.rds

One row per household (clust, nh, clust_nh, total_farm_area_acres).

4.2 Profit_per_acre.R

Purpose: Build total profit per household and profit per acre.

Key Steps:

Load:

agg2.dta → agricultural income/depreciation.

sec8b_farm_land_household_level.rds → land area.

Remove exact duplicates in agg2.

Create clust_nh in agg2.

Keep clust, nh, clust_nh, agri1c, hhagdepn.

Define safe_sum() to handle all-NA sums cleanly.

Aggregate by clust_nh:

total_agri1c = sum of agri1c.

total_depr = sum of hhagdepn.

total_profit = total_agri1c - total_depr.

Inner join with land file on clust_nh.

Compute:

profit_per_acre = total_profit / total_farm_area_acres


(set to NA when land is missing or zero).

Output:

agg2_profit_per_acre_household.rds.

4.3 EDA + Master Build Script

Purpose:
Take the household profit_per_acre data, remove outliers, merge with community & geographic data, run EDA, and create an EDA-ready master file.

Key Inputs:

agg2_profit_per_acre_household.rds

EA_master_community_allmodules.dta

sec0a.dta

Key Steps (Summary):

Outlier removal on profit_per_acre using 1.5 × IQR rule:

Creates agg2_profit_per_acre_household_without_outliers.rds.

Merge with EA-level community master

Join on cluster ID (clust matched to EA_ID + 4000).

Create rural_dummy = 1 where EA exists in community master, else 0.

Save as EDA_master_file.dta.

Attach region & district from sec0a.dta

Build EA-level crosswalk and join on cluster.

Type checks, NA handling & binary variables

Explore structure, missingness.

For health/disease variables, replace NA → 0 only when rural_dummy == 1 (no report treated as “no problem” in rural data; urban stays as missing).

Save EDA master

Final_EDA_master_file.rds — hand-off file to teammate.

EDA & Correlations

Create boxplots of profit_per_acre by key binary covariates (infrastructure, health, education environment, inputs, etc.), saving as EDA_*.png.

Compute and print correlations between profit_per_acre and selected covariates.

