4.5 Mater_file_model.R 

Purpose

Bring in household roster information from sec1.dta (especially:

household head gender,

count of working-age adults 15–50)

Merge this onto your teammate’s file to create the final modeling dataset.

Key Steps

Load & deduplicate sec1.dta

sec1_raw   <- read_dta("sec1.dta")
sec1_clean <- sec1_raw %>% distinct()


Build household-level variables from sec1

Group by clust, nh and compute:

labour_age_15_50_count

labour_age_15_50_count = sum(!is.na(agey) & agey >= 15 & agey <= 50)


head_sex = sex of household head, defined as pid == 1.
Then convert to binary:

is_head_male = case_when(
  head_sex %in% c(1, "1", "M", "m", "Male", "male")   ~ 1,
  head_sex %in% c(2, "2", "F", "f", "Female", "female") ~ 0,
  TRUE ~ NA_real_
)


Create clust_nh again:

clust_nh = paste0(clust, "_", nh)


Final sec1_hh contains:

clust_nh

is_head_male (1 = male head, 0 = female head)

labour_age_15_50_count (number of 15–50-year-olds in the household)

NA diagnostics (optional)

Summarise NA counts for these new variables via na_summary (printed but not saved).

Merge onto teammate’s file

Load:

project <- readRDS("project_EDA_final 1.rds")


Left join:

project_joined <- project %>%
  left_join(sec1_hh, by = "clust_nh")


This preserves all households in project_EDA_final 1.rds and appends roster info where clust_nh matches.

Save final dataset

saveRDS(project_joined, "project_EDA_final_with_sec1.rds")


✅This is final modeling file, containing:

